For Apache/AJP/Tomcat integration the document [Configuring Apache Reverse Proxy Using the AJP Protocol|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+Apache+Reverse+Proxy+Using+the+AJP+Protocol#ConfiguringApacheReverseProxyUsingtheAJPProtocol-Step1%3AConfigureJIRA%27sapplicationserver] should fix the AJP connector string as follows:
{code:xml}
<Connector port="8009" URIEncoding="UTF-8"
 enableLookups="false" redirectPort="8443" protocol="AJP/1.3" />
{code}

e.g. is the correct shortened form of "for example" this is inconsistent in en_US and en_GB

The language_en_US.jar has 
{code}
webfragments.navigation.bar.issues.dropdown.filters=Dopdown ...
{code}

rather than "Drop down"

